social_posts.post_text: I try not to focus too much on these numbers because I can go pretty pretty crazy comparing and despairing, but I am so grateful for every second you’ve given to my songs! Thank youuuu!!!🥰
Happy 2023: the year I finally held a dog! 🐩
Will walk through 6 degrees and snowstorms for smoothies

These peaks and valleys seemed like a fitting place to reflect on my ups and downs:
​
​113 self-administered injections
​25 ish blood draws (I lost count but the scar on my arm remembers)
​18 eggs
​2 finger pricks
​2 intramuscular shots (scare me)
​2 IVs (really scare me)
​0 healthy embryos (so far!)
​
​This 2nd time around things hurt a little less somehow. I’m able to detach my mind from my physical body. The pain is still there, but I separate myself from it. I’m grateful that I even have the chance to experience this pain and this process. Yes, it’s an unmitigated disaster what happened with my frozen eggs, but I have the means and a glimmer of fecundity left in my body that many others my age and younger have lost. So I’m going to see the positive in all I have and try to snatch victory from the jaws of defeat💪🏼💪🏼💪🏼

Maximalism in Miami

72 hours in NYC 🍎🚕❄️
Today was the hardest day physically since I found out my frozen eggs were destroyed. Countless hard days emotionally🎢 but today was intense physical pain. 

I’m alone in NY for an experimental procedure on my ovaries. And when I woke up…well, I wished they would’ve knocked me back out. 

The doctor said there’s a 30% chance it may benefit me to do this all over AGAIN in 2 weeks but gave a disclaimer that the majority of people cannot handle it physically or emotionally. To that I said, “I’ll be back in 2 weeks.” 💪🏼

Most importantly, an angel of a woman contacted me after reading my comment on a New York Times article about egg freezing. She had success after a similar disaster and gave me invaluable information. She lives in NYC and waited during my procedure to walk me back to my hotel!! A complete stranger. Now a friend for life. 🥹❤️

It was so good to be creative with friends and feel like myself again!
I haven’t posted details lately, but I’ve been under anesthesia every month of 2023. June has been my first required break from heavy fertility meds, hormones, and steroids. My body has changed a lot and it has taken a toll physically and mentally. I’ve been writing about it all to share in a book.
In the meantime, wearing this cape made of silver really lifted my spirits💎

Once-in-a-lifetime chance to see the great Joni Mitchell! In 1971, Joni wrote these lyrics to her song “California” which still hold true:
🎶Reading the news and it sure looks bad
They won’t give peace a chance
That was just a dream some of us had🎶
Watch til the end to hear her sing “Shine On.” I can only pray for the light of peace to shine on these inhumanely dark times🤍

River by Joni Mitchell

“If you had not suffered as you have, there would be no depth to you as a human being, no humility, no compassion.” ✨2023✨

I’m doing my best to take care of and appreciate my body and mind for all it has been through this last year. Hope you are doing the same - happy new year🤍
